title: Making File Names Unique
content:
Given an array of strings  of size . You will create  folders in your file system such that, at the  minute, you will create a folder with the name .
Since two files cannot have the same name, if you enter a folder name which is previously used, the system will have a suffix addition to its name in the form of , where,  is the smallest positive integer such that the obtained name remains unique.
Return an array of strings of length  where  is the actual name the system will assign to the  folder when you create it.
